HEADWORD: collard
<hw>collard</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a variety of kale
(<spn>Brassica oleracea</spn>) having smooth leaves; a type of
<isa>colewort</isa>. It is grown in the southern U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
